  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_2' aria-label=\" The State of Himachal Pradesh & Anr. versus JSW Hydro Energy Limited & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('2','2025','2025_7_1104_1143','2025INSC857'); ><font size='4'> <strong>THE STATE OF HIMACHAL PRADESH & ANR.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>JSW HYDRO ENERGY LIMITED & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 7 S.C.R. 1104</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 857</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010007872025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : PAMIDIGHANTAM SRI NARASIMHA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, JOYMALYA BAGCHI</strong><br> Issue for Consideration The primary issues arising for consideration are: first, whether the CERC Regulations, 2019 bar respondent no. 1 from supplying free power to the appellant-State beyond 13%; and second, whether respondent no. 1 could have invoked the High for aligning the Implementation Agreement with the CERC Regulations, 2019. Headnotes&dagger; Electricity Act, 2003 &ndash; CERC (Terms and Conditions of Tariff) Regulations, 2019 &ndash; Regulations 44 and 55 &ndash; Note 3 of Regulation 55 &ndash; Respondent no.1, a generating company,<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 16-07-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 12883/2024</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('2','2025','2025_7_1104_1143','2025INSC857','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split vi